General question: Results related to the intended outcome 2015Question: Summarise results related to the intended outcome (this information will be sent to Open Aid)Answer: The results shown in this report concern the whole duration of the project, from January 2012 to December 2015. 

The overall conclusion is that the project has delivered on a majority of agreed objectives from a rather ambitious work plan. This is the result of close and daily cooperation between the Swedish Police and the Serbian Ministry of Interior (MoI), which allowed for timely planning of activities.

More specifically, the project achieved the following results:

- 60 officials from different organizational units in the MoI have been trained in strategic planning, in order to enable a smoother follow-up of the implementation of the Action Plan for the MoI Development Strategy 2011-2016;
- More than 50 officials from different organizational units in the MoI have been trained in RBM methodology; 7 of them underwent Train-the-Trainer program;
- Development of the mechanism for progress reporting and performance monitoring of the implementation of the Action Plan for Chapter 24 of the acquis has been assisted;
- A number of MoI officials have been trained at the European Institute for Public Administration in Maastricht in topics related to the development of indicators for monitoring and evaluation of projects funded by the EU, integrity systems and anti-corruption measures and impact assessments applied in EU decision-making. The relevance of these trainings is in obtaining a practical understanding of key policy development tools, which will be very useful when developing EU-compatible legislation;
- A study trip to Brussels has been organized for 5 MoI staff members, to meet with the DG Home and DG NEAR and discuss the upcoming negotiation process;
- Change management training has been organized for 60 managers from various organizational units in the MoI. 12 of them became educated trainers. A training manual has also been developed;
- 5 seminars in program budgeting have been organized for the Bureau for Strategic Planning;
- A training on assertive communication has been delivered to the Bureau for Strategic Planning;
- A training on time management has been delivered to the Bureau for Strategic Planning, with the aim to improve their soft skills;
- The general capacity of the Bureau for Strategic Planning for monitoring and reporting on the results connected to the MoI's Action Plan has been greatly enhanced. A uniformed reporting format and methodology have been developed;
- IPA department of the MoI has received assistance in the form of a SOP (Standardized Operation Procedure)/Handbook for project cycle management and a training in PRAG (EU procurement rules);
- Bureau for International Cooperation and EU Integration has been on study trips to Croatia, Slovak Republic, Hungary, Romania and Montenegro to learn about different MoI organizations and experiences from EU accession;
- A proposal for the change of legal framework concerning ILP (Intelligence-Led Policing) has been developed and presented to the Minister. A Handbook for ILP has been finalized and submitted to the Minister for approval;
- 15 analysts and 5 national instructors have been trained in Analyst's Notebook software. 12 users and 3 instructors have been trained in the OIAT analyst method;
- Action Plans for the implementation of ILP in pilot regions of Kraljevo and Novi Sad have been drafted. Operational Leading Groups have been established and have received support;
- A Forensic Training Center in line with the European standards has been established and equipped;
- The curricula for the basic crime scene course and other specialist courses have been designed;
- The document describing the system for the selection of trainers has been designed and integrated in the new SOP;
- A procedure for the recruitment, operational preparation and previous knowledge testing of the candidates has been developed and integrated in the system;
- 20 CSI officers have been trained in line with the new curricula, 17 CSI officers from Serbia and Montenegro have been trained to perform Bloodstain Pattern Analysis, 13 CSI officers have been trained in DVI (Disaster Victim Identification) in line with INTERPOL standards; 27 police officers have been trained as first responders on crime scene, 15 CSI officers have been trained to use VR (Virtual Reality) photo on crime scene, 27 CSI officers have been trained as regional coordinators in charge of crime scenes;
- A good practice manual has been approved and is used in daily work;
- A "skeleton" QMS (Quality Management System) for CSI has been developed;
- National Crime Technical Center received ISO 17025 accreditation from the European Network of Forensic Science Institutes;
- Seminars on gender mainstreaming, increasing gender awareness in strategic planning , gender perspective in ILP, gender analysis in strategic planning and reporting have been organized for a number of MoI officials, enhancing their knowledge and awareness in this important topic;
- A study visit to Sweden has been organized to familiarize the MoI officials with current gender practices of the Swedish Police.
